quran[5]{c,v,t}:
  61,10,"Believers, shall I direct you to a commerce that will deliver you from a grievous chastisement"
  61,11,Have faith in Allah and His Messenger and strive in the Way of Allah with your possessions and your lives. That is better for you if you only knew
  61,12,He will forgive you your sins and will admit you to Gardens beneath which rivers flow. He will lodge you in excellent mansions in the Gardens of eternity. That is the supreme triumph
  61,13,"He will also grant you the other favour that you desire: help from Allah and a victory that will come soon. Give glad tidings of this to the believers"
  61,14,"Believers, become Allah's helpers, as Jesus, son of Mary, said to the disciples: “Who is my helper in (calling people) to Allah?” The disciples had responded by saying: “We are Allah's helpers.” Then a section of the Children of Israel believed and a section rejected the call. Thereafter We aided the believers against their enemies, and they prevailed"